    "updated_at": "2015-08-03T02:31:02Z",
    "body": "Actually, I once wondered why `if` and others do not end with `;`. Now I know the answer!\n\nRequiring them to end with `;` would have brought more consistency, but that would have also been less ergonomic, I think... Was this option considered in the early history of Rust?\n",
